{"info": {"author": "Andrei", "author_email": "andrei.zbikowski@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# Steamy\nSteamy is a lightweight, limited-abstraction interface to both the [public Steam Web API](https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Steam_Web_API) and a custom Steam Market API.\n\n## Public Steam Web API\nTo interface with the public Steam Web API, you must have a [Steam API Key](https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey). To get started, create an instance of the SteamAPI interface:\n\n```\nsteam = SteamAPI(my_api_key)\n```\n\n### Examples\n\nGet a trade offer\n```\noffer = steam.get_trade_offer(offer_id)\nassert offer['tradeofferid'] == offer_id\n```\n\nGet members for a group\n```\nmembers = steam.get_group_members(\"testgroupplzignore\", page=1)\nassert len(members)\n```\n\n### Workshop Interface\nThe SteamAPI interface also provides the ability to query workshop items:\n\n```\nwfile = steam.get_workshop_file(\"447269341\")\nassert isinstance(wfile, WorkshopFile)\nassert wfile.id == \"447269341\"\n```", "description_content_type": null, "docs_url": null, "download_url": "UNKNOWN", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "http://github.com/b1naryth1ef/steamy", "keywords": null, "license": "Apache 2.0", "maintainer": null, "maintainer_email": null, "name": "steamy", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/steamy/", "platform": "UNKNOWN", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/steamy/", "project_urls": {"Download": "UNKNOWN", "Homepage": "http://github.com/b1naryth1ef/steamy"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/steamy/1.0.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": null, "summary": "a library for interacting with the steam API and marketplace", "version": "1.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p># Steamy\nSteamy is a lightweight, limited-abstraction interface to both the [public Steam Web API](<a href=\"https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Steam_Web_API\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Steam_Web_API</a>) and a custom Steam Market API.</p>\n<p>## Public Steam Web API\nTo interface with the public Steam Web API, you must have a [Steam API Key](<a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://steamcommunity.com/dev/apikey</a>). To get started, create an instance of the SteamAPI interface:</p>\n<p><tt>`\nsteam = SteamAPI(my_api_key)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>### Examples</p>\n<p>Get a trade offer\n<tt>`\noffer = steam.get_trade_offer(offer_id)\nassert <span class=\"pre\">offer['tradeofferid']</span> == offer_id\n`</tt></p>\n<p>Get members for a group\n<tt>`\nmembers = <span class=\"pre\">steam.get_group_members(\"testgroupplzignore\",</span> page=1)\nassert len(members)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>### Workshop Interface\nThe SteamAPI interface also provides the ability to query workshop items:</p>\n<p><tt>`\nwfile = <span class=\"pre\">steam.get_workshop_file(\"447269341\")</span>\nassert isinstance(wfile, WorkshopFile)\nassert wfile.id == \"447269341\"\n`</tt></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 1781651, "releases": {"0.0.1": [], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3f120c21c450e25afe86698e083f9e41", "sha256": "d2411c741967bf66190e693310ee28ce1801080c3a64f05476532523958e9181"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "steamy-0.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "3f120c21c450e25afe86698e083f9e41", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 6041, "upload_time": "2015-05-30T01:45:41", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2015-05-30T01:45:41.413722Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/01/1a/3da3f63311309aaf9e3844065a74c6715d6c2a65ad67a775f8532c7245ad/steamy-0.0.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.3": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "915da1de22186bdb9e186d1965e40db6", "sha256": "60b2ac93666fa63ab4a254aca50791fd2c38fd255dd69f338d8dde93db9b4b9f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "steamy-0.0